#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:1
msgid "Apple Silicon with Metal (MLX)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:3
msgid ""
"This document describes how run SGLang on Apple Silicon using [Metal (MLX)]"
"(https://opensource.apple.com/projects/mlx/). If you encounter issues or "
"have questions, please [open an issue](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/"
"issues)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:5
msgid "Install SGLang"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:7
msgid "You can install SGLang using one of the methods below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:9
msgid "Install from Source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:11
msgid ""
"# Use the default branch\n"
"git clone https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang.git\n"
"cd sglang\n"
"\n"
"# Install sglang python package\n"
"pip install --upgrade pip\n"
"rm -f python/pyproject.toml && mv python/pyproject_other.toml python/"
"pyproject.toml\n"
"uv pip install -e \"python[all_mps]\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:22
msgid "Launch of the Serving Engine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:24
msgid "Launch the server with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:26
msgid ""
"SGLANG_USE_MLX=1 python -m sglang.launch_server \\\n"
"  --model <MODEL_ID_OR_PATH> \\\n"
"  --disable-cuda-graph \\\n"
"  --host 0.0.0.0\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:33
msgid "**Key Parameters Explained:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:35
msgid ""
"`SGLANG_USE_MLX=1` - Enables the use of MLX as the SGLang runtime backend "
"(if disabled, SGLang will fall back to `torch.mps`, which has less support)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:36
msgid ""
"`--disable-cuda-graph` - Disables usage of CUDA graph, which is not relevant "
"for Apple Metal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:37
msgid ""
"`--disable-overlap-schedule` - Disables overlap scheduling (enabled/not "
"present by default) achieved using MLX's `async_eval()`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:40
msgid "Benchmarking with Requests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:42
msgid ""
"`sglang.benchmark_one_batch` calls the synchronous prefill/decode methods "
"directly without going through the scheduler and the overlap code path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:44
msgid ""
"`sglang.benchmark_offline_throughput` can toggle overlap scheduling as it "
"uses the scheduler and the overlap code path by using the flag `--disable-"
"overlap-schedule`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:46
msgid "Throughput Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:48
msgid "Basic synchronous one batch throughput:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:49
msgid ""
"SGLANG_USE_MLX=1 python -m sglang.bench_one_batch \\\n"
"  --model-path <MODEL_ID_OR_PATH> \\\n"
"  --disable-cuda-graph \\\n"
"  --tp-size 1 \\\n"
"  --batch-size 1 \\\n"
"  --input-len 60 \\\n"
"  --output-len 10\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:59
msgid "Synchronous offline throughput:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:60
msgid ""
"SGLANG_USE_MLX=1 python -m sglang.bench_offline_throughput \\\n"
"  --model-path <MODEL_ID_OR_PATH> \\\n"
"  --disable-cuda-graph \\\n"
"  --num-prompts 1 \\\n"
"  --disable-overlap-schedule\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:68
msgid "Asynchronous offline throughput:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../platforms/apple_metal.md:69
msgid ""
"SGLANG_USE_MLX=1 python -m sglang.bench_offline_throughput \\\n"
"  --model-path <MODEL_ID_OR_PATH> \\\n"
"  --disable-cuda-graph \\\n"
"  --num-prompts 1\n"
msgstr ""
